	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64121221">If you want to understand why Americans pay much more for much poorer healthcare outcomes, maybe this documentary can highlight exactly what it is that makes US healthcare services so problematic. The doc examines how the world's first National Health Service (the UK's NHS, set up to alleviate the fear of you or anyone in your family getting sick &amp; not being able to care for them adequately) is being stealthily transformed from the principle of healthcare as a right (AKA universal healthcare, which is enshrined in the UN's Declaration of Human Rights) to something more like the US model, i.e. healthcare as a consumer service only for those willing &amp; able to pay, &amp; the effects of this transformation on patients, hospitals, healthcare practitioners, &amp; society in general: <a href="https://thedirtywaronnhs.com/" title="thedirtywaronnhs.com">https://thedirtywaronnhs.com/</a> [thedirtywaronnhs.com] Free to watch here: <a href="https://vimeo.com/446804511" title="vimeo.com">https://vimeo.com/446804511</a> [vimeo.com]</div>
	</div>

